    <p class="sub">Quick answers to the things people usually ask before joining.</p>

    <details>
      <summary>Which plan is right for me?</summary>
      <p>If you'll be here a couple times a week or more and want the gym, <strong>Club</strong> is the best value at $388/mo (about $18/workday). Coming 2 to 3 days a week but don't want the gym? <strong>Cadence</strong> at $288/mo gives you 10 visits. Want your own desk plus 24/7 access? <strong>Resident</strong> at $588/mo includes everything in Club, your dedicated workstation, business address, and 1 hour of meeting room credits each month. Want the wellness amenities too? Add <strong>Premium Wellness</strong> ($140/mo) to any Club or Resident membership. Coming once a week or less? Day passes are $45 each, or grab a 4-pack at $168 (or go monthly at $138/mo for 4 visits recurring). All in the Day Pass section above.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>How does the money-back guarantee work?</summary>
      <p>It's straightforward. <strong>If Den 1880 isn't right for you, we'll refund what you paid.</strong> Talk to the front desk or email hello@den1880.co. We'll review your concern, work with you to make it right, and issue a refund if we can't.</p>
      <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:8px"><strong>Terms:</strong> the money-back guarantee is claimable within the first month of your membership when our service hasn't met expectations. One claim per member. Applies to <strong>Club</strong> and <strong>Resident</strong> memberships only. Day passes (including 4-pack and monthly subscription) and Cadence memberships aren't covered.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>What's the catch with the 2-month minimum?</summary>
      <p>None. Club and Resident members are covered by the money-back guarantee in the first month if our service hasn't met expectations. After that you go month-to-month with 30 days notice to cancel. We use the 2-month minimum because members tell us it takes about three weeks to build a routine here, and we'd rather you actually experience it than churn after a single trial week.</p>
    </details>

